Eph:
Start there.

56:04.495 --> 56:06.862
Wait, wait.

56:06.864 --> 56:08.130
There.

56:10.834 --> 56:12.868
Eph:
What's that
distortion?

56:12.870 --> 56:14.870
Foreman:
I don't know.

56:14.872 --> 56:18.674
It grabs the box
and lifts it off...

56:18.676 --> 56:22.344
up...

56:22.346 --> 56:23.645
That box was
500 pounds.

56:23.647 --> 56:25.414
Nothing could lift
it up like that.

56:25.416 --> 56:28.584
The old man said, "If you have
the coffin, you still have him."

56:30.086 --> 56:31.720
Him.

56:35.658 --> 56:39.228
This footage is only seven
minutes old.

56:39.230 --> 56:42.664
The box is still
in the airport.

57:14.431 --> 57:16.465
Uh huh.

57:27.210 --> 57:30.446
What the hell is that?

57:30.448 --> 57:32.314
Crazy ass white boy.

57:32.316 --> 57:34.950
(engine starts)

57:36.252 --> 57:39.755
(tires squeal)

57:39.757 --> 57:42.524
¶

57:43.660 --> 57:45.594
Come on, come on,
pick up.

57:45.596 --> 57:47.129
Jim, where are you
right now?

57:47.131 --> 57:49.298
At the main garage door
funneling traffic out.

57:49.300 --> 57:50.966
Stop it, stop it!
Stop everyone.

57:50.968 --> 57:52.501
This is an emergency.

57:52.503 --> 57:54.837
You need to seal off the
perimeter of the airport.

57:54.839 --> 57:56.305
That box...

57:56.307 --> 57:58.173
<i>Remember the box</i>
<i>with the markings on it?</i>

57:58.175 --> 58:00.075
Yeah, yeah,
the Berlin cargo omit.

58:00.077 --> 58:01.143
<i>That's the one. </i>

58:01.145 --> 58:02.678
Now listen carefully, Jim.

58:02.680 --> 58:05.781
We need to stop all vehicles big
enough to hold it.

58:05.783 --> 58:08.350
No vans, no trucks, nothing.

58:08.352 --> 58:10.853
<i>No big vehicles.</i>
<i>No exceptions.</i>

58:10.855 --> 58:13.989
Okay, no big vehicles in or out
of the security zone. Got it.

58:13.991 --> 58:15.757
Right, everybody listen up.

58:15.759 --> 58:17.493
I want none of these trucks

58:17.495 --> 58:21.330
<i>big-sized vehicles released</i>
<i>without my authorization.</i>

58:24.200 --> 58:25.501
C'mon...

58:25.503 --> 58:27.536
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

58:29.439 --> 58:32.007
¶

58:42.952 --> 58:46.054
Pull up there, sir,
I'll be right with you.

58:46.056 --> 58:49.091
Shit! Shit, shit!

58:57.867 --> 58:59.501
ID and permit.

58:59.503 --> 59:01.236
Oh, yeah, man.

59:01.238 --> 59:03.605
Crazy what's
happening, huh?

59:12.815 --> 59:15.918
What do you want me
to do with this?

59:15.920 --> 59:18.420
<i>(dog barking)</i>

59:21.357 --> 59:24.726
Step out of the vehicle,
open the cargo area, sir.

59:24.728 --> 59:26.528
Step out of
the vehicle--

59:26.530 --> 59:29.164
- Get the light out of my face!
- Step out of the vehicle.

59:29.166 --> 59:30.666
Can I get my
seat belt?

59:41.511 --> 59:43.512
Hey. What's going
on here?

59:43.514 --> 59:47.182
I asked for ID,
he gave me this.

59:52.956 --> 59:54.890
Oh, well, this is
one of our vehicles.

59:54.892 --> 59:56.091
You can let
him through.

59:56.093 --> 59:57.092
Sir?

59:57.094 --> 59:58.994
I said, let
him through.

1:00:03.399 --> 1:00:05.267
You tell those sons
of bitches I'm done.

1:00:05.269 --> 1:00:07.636
I came through for them
but now I am done.

1:00:07.638 --> 1:00:09.771
You got it?

1:00:14.811 --> 1:00:17.279
Okay, go.

1:00:18.915 --> 1:00:22.618
<i>(electric saw buzzing)</i>

1:00:22.620 --> 1:00:28.890
Bennett:
<i>I have now removed the chest</i>
<i>plate of one of the subjects</i>

1:00:28.892 --> 1:00:30.792
<i>and found...</i>

1:00:30.794 --> 1:00:38.934
abnormal neoplasms
in the heart, liver...

1:00:38.936 --> 1:00:41.670
and kidneys.

1:00:43.339 --> 1:00:47.576
The growths do not seem like
oncological aberrations

1:00:47.578 --> 1:00:55.250
but almost like new, fully
functional organs.

1:00:58.354 --> 1:01:01.757
("Sweet Caroline" playing
on radio)

1:01:07.030 --> 1:01:09.831
(loud clatter)

1:01:26.983 --> 1:01:29.284
(hinge squeaks)

1:01:38.294 --> 1:01:40.762
(squishing sound)

1:01:52.008 --> 1:01:54.209
(gasps)

1:01:58.548 --> 1:02:00.782
(panting)

1:02:03.052 --> 1:02:05.153
What?!

1:02:05.155 --> 1:02:07.422
No!

1:02:07.424 --> 1:02:09.725
Ah!

1:02:09.727 --> 1:02:12.561
(loud clatter)

1:02:14.497 --> 1:02:17.332
(gasping)

1:02:17.334 --> 1:02:21.336
(grunting)

1:02:21.338 --> 1:02:23.438
Agh!

1:02:30.713 --> 1:02:33.281
(growling)

1:02:40.723 --> 1:02:43.024
(gasping)

1:02:45.194 --> 1:02:48.563
(roaring, squealing)

1:02:48.565 --> 1:02:52.968
<i>("Sweet Caroline" continues</i>
<i>playing on radio)</i>

1:02:58.808 --> 1:03:00.675
<i>(sirens)</i>

1:03:04.113 --> 1:03:07.249
Sorry, Eph. Nothing.

1:03:07.251 --> 1:03:08.416
<i>You got anything here?</i>

1:03:08.418 --> 1:03:10.452
Just trying to figure out

1:03:10.454 --> 1:03:15.257
how a 500-pound, 9-foot tall
coffin got up and walked away.

1:03:15.259 --> 1:03:17.392
You called it
a coffin.

1:03:17.394 --> 1:03:18.760
<i>We'll get a break.</i>

1:03:18.762 --> 1:03:19.961
We always do.

1:03:19.963 --> 1:03:22.397
We just gotta find
some place to start.

1:03:25.301 --> 1:03:27.435
This is where
we start.

1:03:27.437 --> 1:03:29.237
What the hell
are those?

1:03:29.239 --> 1:03:31.273
Something new.

1:03:31.275 --> 1:03:33.875
¶

1:03:43.820 --> 1:03:47.789
S-E-T-R-A-K-I-A-N.

1:03:47.791 --> 1:03:49.858
Setrakian?

1:03:49.860 --> 1:03:51.326
What is...
what is that?

1:03:51.328 --> 1:03:52.594
Armenian.

1:03:52.596 --> 1:03:54.095
Is that where
you're from?

1:03:54.097 --> 1:03:56.498
At one time...

1:03:57.867 --> 1:03:59.467
How soon may I leave?

1:03:59.469 --> 1:04:01.269
Well, nothing happens
'til Monday.

1:04:01.271 --> 1:04:02.604
The charges are
filed then.

1:04:02.606 --> 1:04:04.005
It's almost
dawn now.

1:04:06.108 --> 1:04:08.710
(prisoners: shouting)

1:04:12.815 --> 1:04:16.051
Are you the librarian?

1:04:16.053 --> 1:04:18.720
Oh...

1:04:18.722 --> 1:04:22.023
That's some ancient
ink you got there, old man.

1:04:22.025 --> 1:04:23.859
What is it, numbers?

1:04:23.861 --> 1:04:25.327
Yeah, numbers.

1:04:25.329 --> 1:04:28.396
Mean anything?

1:04:30.800 --> 1:04:33.435
Only to me.

1:04:41.310 --> 1:04:44.446
Everything went
as planned.

1:04:45.915 --> 1:04:48.917
Eichhorst:
Love is going to guide
them all back

1:04:48.919 --> 1:04:54.289
to their homes,
to their loved ones.

1:04:56.525 --> 1:04:59.027
Palmer:
Curious detail--

1:04:59.029 --> 1:05:04.232
an old man with a sword was
arrested at the airport.

1:05:05.835 --> 1:05:08.570
The Jew.

1:05:08.572 --> 1:05:10.071
He's still at it.

1:05:10.073 --> 1:05:12.274
After all these years.

1:05:12.276 --> 1:05:14.009
You must admire
him for that.

1:05:14.011 --> 1:05:17.746
I'll take care of him.

1:05:17.748 --> 1:05:19.848
I look out upon
this island

1:05:19.850 --> 1:05:24.519
and I savor what
is to come--

1:05:24.521 --> 1:05:27.022
purity.

1:05:27.024 --> 1:05:30.258
Mr. Fitzwilliam...

1:05:30.260 --> 1:05:31.893
a sentimental man

1:05:31.895 --> 1:05:33.929
would venture out
into the city tonight

1:05:33.931 --> 1:05:38.633
to walk these streets
one last time...

1:05:38.635 --> 1:05:42.137
before the fall.

1:05:42.139 --> 1:05:43.905
Do you require
anything else, sir?

1:05:43.907 --> 1:05:45.407
No.

1:05:45.409 --> 1:05:47.275
For the first
time in my life

1:05:47.277 --> 1:05:51.613
I have everything
I need.

1:05:56.752 --> 1:05:59.287
¶

1:06:08.130 --> 1:06:11.866
(Latino hip hop
playing on radio)

1:06:18.474 --> 1:06:21.743
(phone rings)

1:06:21.745 --> 1:06:23.812
Hello?

1:06:23.814 --> 1:06:26.181
(speaking Spanish)

1:06:28.117 --> 1:06:29.417
Huh? No, Mommy, no.

1:06:29.419 --> 1:06:31.019
I'm not smoking.
You kidding me or what?

1:06:31.021 --> 1:06:32.620
I'm working.

1:06:32.622 --> 1:06:34.856
<i>Just called to check in to see</i>
<i>what you're up to.</i>

1:06:34.858 --> 1:06:36.157
<i>Is Crispin home?</i>

1:06:36.159 --> 1:06:37.158
He is.

1:06:37.160 --> 1:06:39.861
(speaking Spanish)

1:06:39.863 --> 1:06:42.163
Mama, one beer left.

1:06:42.165 --> 1:06:43.531
Why do you do
this to me?

1:06:43.533 --> 1:06:45.133
How many times do
I gotta tell you?

1:06:45.135 --> 1:06:46.368
I'm making his breakfast.

1:06:46.370 --> 1:06:48.169
Gus:
<i>I'm getting on the bridge now.</i>

1:06:48.171 --> 1:06:49.504
<i>I'll be home in an hour.</i>

1:06:49.506 --> 1:06:50.705
Mama:
<i>Okay.</i>

1:06:50.707 --> 1:06:54.876
(speaking Spanish)

1:06:56.979 --> 1:07:01.082
I don't know what you are but
you're bringing me good luck.

1:07:02.551 --> 1:07:05.120
(singing along with radio
in Spanish)

1:07:11.861 --> 1:07:18.133
Setrakian:
Love, you see, is the one force
<i>that cannot be explained</i>

1:07:18.135 --> 1:07:21.870
<i>cannot be broken down</i>
<i>into a chemical process.</i>

1:07:21.872 --> 1:07:25.707
<i>It is the beacon that</i>
<i>guides us back home</i>

1:07:25.709 --> 1:07:27.642
<i>when no one is there</i>

1:07:27.644 --> 1:07:32.414
<i>and the light</i>
<i>that illuminates our loss.</i>

1:07:32.416 --> 1:07:36.217
<i>Its absence robs us of</i>
<i>all pleasure</i>

1:07:36.219 --> 1:07:39.320
<i>of our capacity for joy.</i>

1:07:39.322 --> 1:07:45.427
<i>It makes our nights darker and</i>
<i>our days gloomier.</i>

1:07:52.835 --> 1:07:54.602
<i>But when we find love</i>

1:07:54.604 --> 1:07:59.407
<i>no matter how wrong, how sad</i>
<i>or how terrible</i>

1:07:59.409 --> 1:08:01.776
<i>we cling to it.</i>

1:08:01.778 --> 1:08:04.412
<i>It gives us our strength.</i>

1:08:04.414 --> 1:08:06.915
<i>It holds us upright.</i>

1:08:08.717 --> 1:08:13.288
<i>It feeds on us</i>
<i>and we feed on it.</i>

1:08:45.321 --> 1:08:49.824
(sobbing)
Emma... Emma...

1:08:49.826 --> 1:08:52.994
(tap on window)

1:09:00.102 --> 1:09:03.004
(wind whistles)

1:09:05.908 --> 1:09:08.176
(speaking French)

1:09:31.100 --> 1:09:33.168
(crying) Emma...

1:09:33.170 --> 1:09:36.171
Oh, baby...

1:09:44.146 --> 1:09:46.915
(speaking French)

1:09:53.289 --> 1:09:56.958
Setrakian:
<i>Love is our grace.</i>

1:09:58.327 --> 1:10:02.263
<i>Love is our downfall.</i>
